# Pila's Dockerfile has no COPY/ADD instructions — the build context is
# never consulted. Excluding everything keeps `nerdctl build` from shipping
# .git, tests, caches, etc. into the build daemon (which on Colima must
# traverse the host-to-VM bridge). The orchestrator source is bind-mounted
# at runtime, not baked in.
#
# We negate Dockerfile + .dockerignore so legacy builders (older `docker
# build` / some podman modes) that honor `*` literally still find them.
# Modern BuildKit always reads the Dockerfile regardless, so the negations
# are belt-and-suspenders for cross-tool compatibility.
*
!Dockerfile
!.dockerignore
